    "body": "## Purpose\n\nCreative/product foundation for Stage 6 Step 9 before Codex implementation.\n\nThis PR remains deliberately **draft** and **documentation/data only**. It does not modify runtime/game code and is not frozen implementation authority.\n\n## Authority\n\nBaseline current main: `7673f3487b0dd52c0c5cb2c7826f4e3fe5cc570e`.\n\nTarget profiles: `RU_BOOMER / RU_GEN_X / RU_MILLENNIAL / RU_ZOOMER / RU_ALPHA`.\n\nRule: `NO FALSE OR MISUSED SLANG`, not `NO SLANG`. Russian cultural lanes must not be produced by translating/mixing foreign generational culture.\n\n## Completed foundation steps\n\n- [x] 1. `FULL_ALPHA_RUSSIAN_FIRST_REWRITE`\n- [x] 2. `RU_CULTURAL_AUTHENTICITY_PASS B/X/M/Z/A`\n- [x] 3. `FRESH_CURRENT_MAIN_INVENTORY`\n- [x] 4. `GAP_CLOSURE`\n- [ ] 5. `USER_REVIEW` - consolidated gateway ready, explicit approval/corrections required\n- [ ] 6. `FREEZE + SHA256` - blocked only by Step 5 approval\n- [ ] 7. `CODEX_IMPLEMENTATION` - blocked by frozen hash and actual implementation preflight\n\n`STAGE 6: NOT COMPLETE`\n\n## Step 3 - fresh current-main inventory COMPLETE\n\nArtifacts:\n\n- `STAGE6_STEP9_FRESH_CURRENT_MAIN_INVENTORY_V1.md`\n- `stage6_step9_fresh_current_main_inventory_v1.json`\n\nThe historical uploaded seed at `e94e4bcb888f4a1e54b2879e3a810118e53a62d9` remains historical evidence only. Its `1930 / 853 / 306` figures are not relabeled as fresh current-main totals.\n\nFresh inventory is bound to:\n\n- exact current-main SHA;\n- active `index.html` runtime script graph;\n- exact current blob SHAs for copy-bearing source families;\n- late `ui/ui-profile-visual-tone-repair.js` presentation authority;\n- source/docs mirror identity evidence;\n- semantic-family classification for player-facing, mechanic-locked, dev-only, legacy/orphan and mirror-alias text.\n\nFresh source proves:\n\n- Gen X has a canonical birth-year band but is not first-class in supported text/presentation routing;\n- current final presentation authority still has only four profile keys;\n- Alpha retains partial Zoomer-baseline inheritance architecture;\n- multiple source/docs pairs currently drift and require targeted reconciliation rather than blind overwrite.\n\n## Step 4 - gap closure COMPLETE\n\nArtifact:\n\n- `STAGE6_STEP9_GAP_CLOSURE_V1.md`\n\nExplicit dispositions now exist for:\n\n- first-class Gen X plumbing;\n- explicit five-profile mapping / no accidental inheritance;\n- four-profile late presentation authority;\n- start/onboarding routing;\n- COP/CAP/shared Millennial fallback families;\n- NPC role/profile pools;\n- source/docs mirror drift;\n- disabled P2P decision `HIDE_DISABLED_P2P_BLOCK_UNTIL_FEATURE_ENABLED`;\n- `npcArrest*` legacy/orphan zero-callsite cleanup gate;\n- accessibility intentional sharing;\n- mechanic-canon locks;\n- unified PR #258 toast architecture;\n- composed wrapper placeholder discipline;\n- hardcoded fallback handling.\n\nNo source/product/structure item remains an unclassified \"guess later\" gap.\n\n## Step 5 - ready for user review\n\nGateway:\n\n- `STAGE6_STEP9_USER_REVIEW_PACKAGE_V1.md`\n\nCandidate precedence is fixed:\n\n1. direct user/source-product decisions;\n2. exact RU cultural-pass corrections;\n3. Alpha Russian-first exact overlay;\n4. Batch 1-4 base matrices;\n5. dedicated start/NPC packs;\n6. voice bibles/cultural/slang rules as constraints.\n\nUser approval is intentionally not inferred from continued work instructions.\n\n## Freeze + implementation prep\n\nPrepared:\n\n- `STAGE6_STEP9_FREEZE_AND_IMPLEMENTATION_PREP_V1.md`\n- updated `STAGE6_STEP9_CODEX_IMPLEMENTATION_CONTRACT.md`\n- updated `STAGE6_STEP9_CREATIVE_REVIEW_INDEX.md`\n\nAfter explicit user review:\n\n1. resolve exact overlays + corrections;\n2. emit frozen Markdown;\n3. emit frozen JSON;\n4. compute SHA-256 over exact JSON bytes;\n5. bind exact implementation scope to then-current main;\n6. run mandatory Codex model preflight;\n7. execute serialized implementation waves;\n8. user runs Safari acceptance.\n\nCodex remains unauthorized until the frozen hash exists.\n\n## Structural invariants\n\n- mechanics/economy/REP/points/influence/battle/NPC behavior unchanged;\n- Gen X cannot be implemented as alias/fallback;\n- Alpha cannot satisfy frozen rows through accidental Zoomer inheritance;\n- intentional shared copy must be explicit;\n- PR #258 unified stat-toast coalescing survives;\n- disabled P2P is hidden, not enabled;\n- source/docs drift is reconciled only in owned hunks;\n- Stage 6 cannot be COMPLETE until user-visible Safari acceptance passes.\n\n## Next action\n\n`USER_REVIEW_STEP9_CONSOLIDATED_COPY_PACKAGE`\n",
